President Muhammadu Buhari has scheduled to proceed for another medical trip to London, the United Kingdom, on Friday.
The Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, in a statement in Abuja on Thursday, explained that the President will be making the trip to London for a scheduled medical follow-up. The SA Media said that  the President would return to the country in the second week of July.
It was highlighted that the President has been scheduled for about three months trip to London. He was in the United Kingdom on March 30 for a routine medical check-up, which Adesina said was a routine medical check. The President came back to Nigeria on April 15, after about two weeks.
